 about osa  awards  career  directories   video  newsroom  help home    biographies stephen d fantone rate this page       stephen d fantone for the last thirty years stephen d fantone founder has been president of optikos corporation headquartered in wakefield massachusetts dr fantone attended massachusetts institute of technology where he received bachelor’s degrees in both electrical engineering and management  in  he was awarded a phd degree in optics from the institute of optics at the university of rochester he began his career with polaroid corporation and later went on to found optikos dr fantone is a senior lecturer in the mechanical engineering department at mit serves on the boards of zygo corporation rofinsinar technologies inc the pioneer institute for public policy research the hertz foundation and the optical society osa dr fantone is a recognized expert in optical engineering and optical product development has served on numerous program review panels has provided expert testimony on patent infringement and trade secret litigation cases and has been awarded over  patents covering a broad range of optical technologies an osa member since  fantone has been serving as a volunteer in many different capacities since   he was elected a fellow member in  and was awarded the distinguished service award in  since  fantone has served as treasurer of the optical society and as member of the board of directors and the executive committee he has chaired the finance committee the audit committee the investment subcommittee the key results oversight committee the ceo compensation committee plus several ad hoc committees  he has served as treasurer of the osa foundation since  and is an active donor as well as member of the optics trust  he has served in key roles across the society including the former engineering council land medal committee nominating committee applied optics and international optical design conference program committees osa awards won stephen d 